{{Infobox park | name = National Herbal Park | alt_name = {{my|အမျိုးသား ဆေးဖက်ဝင် အပင်များ ပန်းခြံ}} | photo = National Herbal Park.jpg | photo_width = | photo_caption = Entrance to the park | type = [[Urban park]] | location = [[Naypyidaw]] | coords = | area = {{convert|200|acre|km2}} | created = 2008 | operator = | visitation_num = | status = Open all year }}
The '''National Herbal Park''' ({{lang-my|အမျိုးသား ဆေးဖက်ဝင် အပင်များ ပန်းခြံ}}) is a {{convert|200|acre|km2|sing=on}} park located near the Naypyidaw-Taungnyo Road in [[Naypyidaw]], [[Burma|Myanmar]]. Over 20,000 herbal and [[Herbalism|medicinal plants]], representing over 700 species from the various [[Administrative divisions of Burma|states and divisions of Myanmar]], are grown in the park. The herbal park is part of the government's efforts to protect and preserve the herbs from depletion and extinction and to keep alive the country's traditional system of medicines. It opened on 4 January 2008.<ref>[http://www.aseancultureandinformation.org/coci/atn1.php?id=219 Myanmar National Herbal Park]</ref> There is no entry fee.
